docs.abstract: The Digital Markets Act is the most sweeping legislation to regulate tech since a European privacy law was passed in 2018.
docs.snippet: The Digital Markets Act is the most sweeping legislation to regulate tech since a European privacy law was passed in 2018.
docs.lead_paragraph: GÖTTINGEN, Germany — The European Union agreed on Thursday to one of the world’s most far-reaching laws to address the power of the biggest tech companies, potentially reshaping app stores, online advertising, e-commerce, messaging services and other everyday digital tools.

headline.main: E.U. Takes Aim at Big Tech’s Power With Landmark Digital Act
headline.print_headline: Europe Agrees On Law to Curb Big Tech’s Might

docs.abstract: The backlash underscored the difficulties some technology companies face in limiting the spread of Russian propaganda.

docs.lead_paragraph: Far-right influencers have often encouraged people to use the small privacy-focused search engine DuckDuckGo instead of Google, saying that the giant search engine censored conservative ideas.

headline.main: The far right complains after the search engine DuckDuckGo vows to limit Russian propaganda.
headline.print_headline: DuckDuckGo Draws Anger From Far Right

docs.abstract: The company aims to be “carbon negative” by the end of the decade, but its emissions rose sharply in the most recent year measured.
docs.snippet: The company aims to be “carbon negative” by the end of the decade, but its emissions rose sharply in the most recent year measured.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft has an ambitious plan to cut its carbon emissions. But on Thursday, the company reported a big increase in the greenhouse gases emanating from its operations and its products, a reminder of the challenges that companies face as they try to clean up their businesses.

headline.main: Microsoft’s Pursuit of Climate Goals Runs Into Headwinds
headline.print_headline: As Emissions Rise, Microsoft Keeps Its Climate Goals

docs.abstract: After years of talks about the need for public-private partnerships to combat cyberattacks, the war in Ukraine is stress-testing the system.
docs.snippet: After years of talks about the need for public-private partnerships to combat cyberattacks, the war in Ukraine is stress-testing the system.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Last Wednesday, a few hours before Russian tanks began rolling into Ukraine, alarms went off inside Microsoft’s Threat Intelligence Center, warning of a never-before-seen piece of “wiper” malware that appeared aimed at the country’s government ministries and financial institutions.

headline.main: As Tanks Rolled Into Ukraine, So Did Malware. Then Microsoft Entered the War.
headline.print_headline: Tech Giants on Alert To Foil Cyberattacks

docs.abstract: In a court filing, the conservative group assailed prosecutors for concealing the action in a proceeding from the investigation of how it acquired Ashley Biden’s diary.

docs.lead_paragraph: The conservative group Project Veritas said on Tuesday that the Justice Department began secretly seizing a trove of its internal communications in late 2020, just weeks after learning that the group had obtained a copy of President Biden’s daughter’s diary.

headline.main: Project Veritas Says Justice Dept. Secretly Seized Its Emails
